With Geryon defeated, Herakles surveys the field of battle, his breathing heavy but his resolve unbroken. He gathers the cattle and begins leading them toward the shore.
Having vanquished Geryon and his guardians, Herakles herded the prized cattle, their golden hides gleaming under the sun, toward his ship.\
Though the journey back to Mycenae would be long, his victory was assured.
